# Data & Media

## Runtime data

- `data/*.json` — catalogs (video_cues, sound_cues, light_scenes, dramaturgy_rules, etc.)
- `data/inszenierungen/{uuid}.json` — persisted Teil 2 productions
- Do not change schemas without migration path and tests

## Media assets

- `media/video/` — OSC command lists, CSV mappings (often local, not always in git)
- `media/light/`, `media/sound/` — stage definitions
- Do not assume `media/video/` exists from git alone

## Import scripts

Regenerate catalogs from source files:

```bash
make avatar-import   # Textzuordnung → avatar_speech.json, OSC lists
make video-import    # Videozuordnung → video_cues.json, OSC ohne Avatare
```

Scripts: `backend/scripts/import_avatar_textzuordnung.py`, `import_video_zuordnung.py`

After import: run relevant catalog tests and spot-check one cue in the generated JSON.
